BikeSack

Class Sensor

  • java.lang.Object
    • BikeSack.Sensor

  • public class Sensor
extends java.lang.Object
    The Sensors provide data to the BikeSack system about the current physical state of the motorbike. These are currently manipulated via keyboard input, but could also be connected to real sensors.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    DevTeam1

      • toggle

        public void toggle()
            throws SensorException
        Toggles a Sensor between minimum (off) and maximum (on) values. If a Sensor is anywhere above the minimum value, it will set it to minimum. Otherwise the Sensor will be set to maximum.
        Throws:
        SensorException - If value is attempted to be set outside min/max range

      • toggle

        public void toggle(int onValue)
            throws SensorException
        Toggles a Sensor between minimum (off) and specified (on) value. If a Sensor is anywhere above the minimum value, it will set it to minimum. Otherwise the Sensor will be set to the specified value.
        Parameters:
        onValue - The value that will be considered as "on" when toggling
        Throws:
        SensorException - If value is attempted to be set outside min/max range

      • increase

        public void increase()
              throws SensorException
        Increase the current Sensor value by INCREMEMENT amount.
        Throws:
        SensorException - If the value of the sensor is increased past the Sensor's maximum value

      • decrease

        public void decrease()
              throws SensorException
        Decrease the current Sensor value by INCREMEMENT amount.
        Throws:
        SensorException - If the value of the sensor is decreased past the Sensor's minimum value
